events.description: The release of preliminary estimates for the annual inflation rate in the Netherlands for January 2026.

facts.fact_text: The annual inflation rate in the Netherlands slowed to 2.4% in January 2026.

evidences.evidence_text: The annual inflation rate in the Netherlands eased to 2.4% in January 2026 from 2.8% in the previous month, according to preliminary estimates.

facts.fact_text: Price growth for food, beverages, and tobacco slowed to 2.0% in January.

evidences.evidence_text: price growth slowed across most product groups, particularly food, beverages, and tobacco (2.0% vs 3.1% in December).

facts.fact_text: Energy prices including motor fuels rebounded to 0.4% in January.

evidences.evidence_text: On the other hand, energy prices including motor fuels rebounded (0.4% vs -0.4%).

facts.fact_text: HICP-based annual inflation was estimated at 2.2% in January.

evidences.evidence_text: HICP-based annual inflation, which excludes owner-occupied housing costs, was estimated at 2.2%, down from 2.7% in December.

claims.claim_text: Consumer prices were expected to decrease by 0.7% on a monthly basis.

evidences.evidence_text: On a monthly basis, consumer prices were expected to fall by 0.7%, following a 0.2% increase in the previous month.

evidence.evidence_text: price growth slowed across most product groups, particularly food, beverages, and tobacco (2.0% vs 3.1% in December).
On the other hand, energy prices including motor fuels rebounded (0.4% vs -0.4%).
Inflation also moderated for industrial goods excluding energy and motor fuels (0.6% vs 0.9%) and for services (3.9% vs 4.1%).
